,'2014-03-28 08:16:28','',90,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/modern-IT.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2012,1,'2014-03-28 08:17:16','2014-03-28 08:17:16','','','','inherit','open','open','','modernit-description','','','2014-03-28 08:17:16','2014-03-28 08:17:16','',90,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/modernIT-description.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2059,1,'2014-04-01 08:42:19','2014-04-01 08:42:19','','PRODUCT','','publish','open','closed','','product','','','2016-09-12 05:31:01','2016-09-12 05:31:01','',320,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=2059',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(2080,1,'2014-04-01 10:56:58','2014-04-01 10:56:58','','Company','','publish','open','closed','','company','','','2016-09-12 05:31:01','2016-09-12 05:31:01','',670,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=2080',20,'nav_menu_item','',0),(2093,1,'2014-04-01 11:53:26','2014-04-01 11:53:26','','News','','publish','open','open','','news','','','2014-12-08 06:22:22','2014-12-08 06:22:22','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=2093',7,'nav_menu_item','',0),(2097,42,'2014-03-31 23:49:38','2014-03-31 23:49:38','<p><a href=\"http://www.mckinsey.com/Insights/Business_Technology/IT_under_pressure_McKinsey_Global_Survey_results\">McKinsey’s latest global survey</a> on business technology shows a challenging dichotomy – IT is more strategic than ever to businesses, but IT shortcomings are more acute.</p>\r\n<p>[caption id=\"attachment_4533\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"354\"]<a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Man4.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-4533 \" alt=\"Showing IT’s Value To The Business\" src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Man4.jpg\" width=\"354\" height=\"284\" /></a> How do you do more with less?[/caption]</p>\r\n<p>It is great news that business executives believe that IT can make a difference, but with it comes expectations that corporate IT will deliver the kind of services that consumer grade cloud and mobile applications offer them outside of the office. The rising bar that business stakeholders place on IT is one of the biggest challenges that face IT operations management.</p>\r\n<p>McKinsey notes that 64% of executives say their budgets for new investments will increase next year, up from 55% in 2012, though they are evenly split on whether operational spending will increase or decrease. Executives also expect IT to spend less on infrastructure and more on innovation and analytics. It makes sense that they want to invest more in core business applications. But less investment in infrastructure doesn\'t mean that managing new and existing infrastructure gets a break.</p>\r\n<p>How do you do “more with less” while meeting the escalating business pressure on IT?</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><b>Align to the business</b>. Seems like an obvious statement, but can you manage your IT infrastructure using a service-oriented lens? Can you monitor for SLA breach thresholds and map IT elements to the business applications and services that they affect? Report IT performance in a business relevant way to tie IT operations and investments closer to the critical business functions that they enable.</li>\r\n<li><b>Optimize your tools. </b>Costs will continue to mount from managing legacy infrastructure with complex enterprise footprint tools and investing in point solutions. If “rip and replace” of your IT operations management tools is unrealistic, find a solution that integrates with multiple point tools so that you have one interface to manage across platforms.</li>\r\n<li><b>Save time. </b>In the survey, the number of IT respondents who said that their organization was effective in managing the IT infrastructure decreased 14%. Look for IT operations management platforms with broad technology integration across your IT elements and vendors – take your people out of multiple management tools to do their job. Increase your limited people resources productivity to free more time to spend on IT projects aligned with strategic business initiatives.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Vistara can help you meet these needs and more with an IT operations management solution that delivers IT operations lifecycle management capabilities spanning physical, virtual, cloud and application elements. Contact Vistara today to learn more.</p>','Showing IT’s Value To The Business','','publish','open','open','','mckinsey-showing-it-business-value','','','2014-09-19 04:42:38','2014-09-19 04:42:38','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=2097',0,'post','',0),(2098,1,'2014-04-01 13:18:50','2014-04-01 13:18:50','Human heads with question mark, dollar, arrow and bulb symbol. \"Dream team\" concept.','','','inherit','open','open','','business-people','','','2014-04-01 13:18:50','2014-04-01 13:18:50','',2097,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Man4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2116,1,'2014-04-01 14:16:14','2014-04-01 14:16:14','','Partners','','publish','open','open','','partners','','','2014-12-08 06:22:22','2014-12-08 06:22:22','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=2116',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(2145,1,'2014-04-02 07:13:04','2014-04-02 07:13:04','','','','inherit','open','open','','converged-infrastructure-2','','','2014-04-02 07:13:04','2014-04-02 07:13:04','',1664,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Converged-Infrastructure.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2148,1,'2014-04-02 07:28:55','2014-04-02 07:28:55','','','','inherit','open','open','','devops-enablement-2','','','2014-04-02 07:28:55','2014-04-02 07:28:55','',349,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/DevOps-Enablement.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2150,1,'2014-04-02 07:45:31','2014-04-02 07:45:31','<section class=\"section\">\r\n<div class=\"container static-content\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-9\"><h1>Case Study: Netskope Succeeds with Modern IT Operations Management and DevOps Using Vistara</h1></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-3 tube20y\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.netskope.com/\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/NSK-logo-200.png\" alt=\"NSK-logo-200\" width=\"200\" height=\"35\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2151\" /></a></div></div>\r\n<h2>About Netskope</h2>\r\n<p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.netskope.com/\">Netskope</a> is the cloud app analytics and policy company. Unlike traditional tools, Netskope performs deep analytics and lets decision-makers create policies to protect corporate data as well as optimize cloud app usage quickly, easily and at scale. With Netskope, people get their favorite cloud apps and the business can move fast, with confidence.</p>\r\n<h2>The Challenge</h2>\r\n<p>Netskope must monitor access to over 2600 cloud apps by the employees of its customers. To enable rapid innovation, Netskope has implemented the DevOps model, so engineering and operations must collaborate seamlessly on product development and deployment. As a rapidly growing startup, Netskope must be able to scale its infrastructure rapidly. Operations team members around the world must work together to keep its solution running 24/7. Finally, everything Netskope does must be done with state of the art security. Its operations must pass stringent Sarbanes-Oxley certification audits.</p>\r\n<h2>The Solution</h2>\r\n<p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.netskope.com/\">Netskope</a> chose Vistara to enable modern IT operations management and DevOps.</p>\r\n<h3>Unified IT Operations Management</h3>\r\n<p>Vistara gives Netskope’s DevOps team a unified view of all of its worldwide physical and virtual infrastructure on-premise and on private clouds and public clouds. Engineers can easily browse elements, monitor their status and the alerts they generate, and manage them from within Vistara.</p>\r\n<h3>Asset Management Over the Lifecycle</h3>\r\n<p>Elements are automatically discovered by Vistara and managed over their lifecycle. “Vistara not only manages IT operations, it also handles inventory, contracts, when things were deployed, and when they are up for renewal, all in a single solution, all in a single pane of glass,” says Rob Cameron, Principal Software Engineer at Netskope.</p>\r\n<h3>Customizable Monitoring Templates</h3>\r\n<p>Netskope has benefited from Vistara’s large library of monitoring templates for elements throughout the stack from all major vendors. Netskope applied templates implementing best practices determined through managing all of Vistara’s customer networks and was easily able to extend and customize those templates to meet its own needs.</p>\r\n<h3>Secure Remote Management</h3>\r\n<p>“The security piece sold me alone,” says Cameron. Engineers log in to Vistara with YubiKey two-factor authentication. Because Vistara securely stores and manages login credentials for IT elements, no further authentications or VPN infrastructure are necessary. Vistara’s role-based acess controls grant each engineer access to the elements they are authorized to view and manage.</p>\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #f3f3f3; padding: 15px;\"><i>“Over the years, we have seen the things that don’t work and Vistara didn’t have those things. We no longer have to go through thousands of command prompt sessions to figure out what the issue is. Vistara helps us detect and resolve issues automatically.”</i><p></p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: right;\">&mdash; Rob Cameron, Principal Software Engineer, Netskope</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Session Recording for Compliance</h3>\r\n<p>Every administrative access session and every action by every administrator is automatically recorded by Vistara for later playback and audit compliance. “Our auditors said that this was light years ahead of what they typically see,” says Cameron. Session recording also makes it easy for one engineer show another how they solved a problem. “There’s no explaining,” says Cameron. “You just give them the session recording and they can see what you did.”</p>\r\n<h3>Unified Alert, Incident, and Problem Management</h3>\r\n<p>Vistara enables Netskope’s engineers to see incoming alerts from all of their IT elements through a single pane of glass. Because of Vistara’s built-in support for incident and problem management, there’s no need for a separate service management solution. Engineers can see the entire history of an alert and how they responded within a single solution.</p>\r\n<h3>Patch and Configuration Management</h3>\r\n<p>Vistara automatically ensures that all of Netskope’s servers stay up to date with the latest patch releases. Vistara also manages the configuration of all of Netskope’s network devices and automatically backs up configurations every time a change is made to enable easy rollback if needed.</p>\r\n<h3>Broad Support Across Platforms and Vendors</h3>\r\n<p>“What I really love with Vistara is that I don’t have to worry about whether I’m using VMware vCenter&reg;, Citrix XenServer&reg;, or OpenStack&reg;; I can use the tools that I need and not have the vendor dictate what I have to use,” adds Cameron. “I choose; Vistara makes it happen and come together in a single pane of glass.”</p>\r\n<h3>Application Management and Custom Dashboards</h3>\r\n<p>Vistara provides customizable application-specific monitoring dashboards with health, performance, and availability information. Vistara also gives the DevOps team a unified heads-up dashboard for seeing the status of the entire network at a glance.</p>\r\n<h3>A Strong Partnership for Success</h3>\r\n<p>“With Vistara there’s no argument,” says Cameron. “We sit on the same side of the table and solve problems together. They’ve been very responsive and have enhanced the application within days, not months, when we needed it. I believe that a vendor should be a partner, and with Vistara we have that. I’m very excited to see what the future holds with Vistara.”</p>\r\n<h2>About Vistara</h2>\r\n<p>Vistara provides a comprehensive SaaS solution for modern IT operations that is used by over 1000 customers. Vistara automatically discovers a customer’s entire distributed IT infrastructure and enables customers to unify their IT operations, manage public and private clouds, and deliver self-service IT. To learn more about Vistara, visit <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com\">http://www.vistarait.com</a>, email <a href=\"mailto:sales@vistarait.com\">sales@vistarait.com</a>, or call toll-free 1-855-VISTARA (1-855-847-8272).</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>','Netskope Modern IT Operations Case Study','','private','open','open','','netskope-modern-it-operations-case-study','','','2015-07-24 06:08:43','2015-07-24 06:08:43','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?page_id=2150',0,'page','',0),(2151,1,'2014-04-02 07:43:21','2014-04-02 07:43:21','','NSK-logo-200','','inherit','open','open','','nsk-logo-200','','','2014-04-02 07:43:21','2014-04-02 07:43:21','',2150,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/NSK-logo-200.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2157,1,'2014-04-02 08:12:40','2014-04-02 08:12:40','<section class=\"section\">\r\n<div class=\"container static-content\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div>\r\n<h1>Senior Sales Executive (Enterprise Software, San Jose, California)</h1>\r\n<p>Vistara is looking for a Senior Sales Executive with experience selling IT business solutions and services specifically in the infrastructure space. The position requires prospecting key decision makers to identify and prioritize new business opportunities, effectively presenting products, services and solutions, and most importantly closing the sale. The right candidate will need to demonstrate the ability to engage prospects and manage customers throughout the entire customer lifecycle.  The candidate will be responsible to close business both directly and through channel partners.</p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: 13px;\">Department: </strong>Sales</p>\r\n<p><strong>Title of the role:</strong> Senior Sales Executive</p>