<div class=\"table-nth\">\r\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"2\" cellpadding=\"2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow: 0; mso-yfti-firstrow: yes;\">\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Consume different services without creating vulnerabilities and enable different services to work seamlessly by configuring them in exactly the same way.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow: 1;\">\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Deliver transparency into the quality of IT services delivered versus the cost of such services.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow: 2;\">\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Get up and running in days, not years, with a pre-integrated software-as-a-service solution.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow: 3; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes;\">\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Establish formalized service levels with business constituents with the ability to measure and report against those service levels.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow: 3; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes;\">\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Manage different different types of devices across business units, locations and teams in today\'s dynamic business environment.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-5\"><iframe src=\"http://info.vistarait.com/unified-it-operations-management-for-modern-it\" height=\"420\" width=\"350\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both;\"></div>\r\n<style><!--\r\ntr { background:#f4f4f4; border:2px solid #fff;} tr td{ border:1px solid #fff; } .hs-form label{font-weight:normal;} .tableyes{ background:url(\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/tickyes.png\"); background-position:center center; background-repeat:no-repeat; } .hs-button primary large {float:right !important} .primary {float:right !important} .hs-button {float:right !important} tr:nth-child(even) {     background-color: #ebebeb; }\r\n--></style></div>\r\n</section>','Unified IT Operations Management for Modern IT','','publish','open','open','','unified-it-operations-management-for-modern-it-solution-brief','','','2014-04-17 11:39:44','2014-04-17 11:39:44','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?page_id=2823',0,'page','',0),(2829,1,'2014-04-11 02:09:48','2014-04-11 02:09:48','','','','inherit','open','open','','vistara-3-4-blog-feed','','','2014-04-11 02:09:48','2014-04-11 02:09:48','',2425,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Vistara-3.4-Blog-Feed.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2830,1,'2014-04-11 02:11:42','2014-04-11 02:11:42','','','','inherit','open','open','','vistara-3-4-blog-feed-2','','','2014-04-11 02:11:42','2014-04-11 02:11:42','',2425,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Vistara-3.4-Blog-Feed1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2835,1,'2014-04-11 02:39:06','2014-04-11 02:39:06','','showing-IT-value','','inherit','open','open','','showing-it-value','','','2014-04-11 02:39:06','2014-04-11 02:39:06','',2097,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/showing-IT-value.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2872,1,'2014-04-11 05:27:08','2014-04-11 05:27:08','<section class=\"section\">\r\n<div class=\"container static-content\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\r\n<h1>Marketing Manager (Enterprise Software, San Jose, CA)</h1>\r\n<p>Vistara is a startup providing a comprehensive SaaS solution for modern IT operations. Vistara is looking for a Marketing Manager to help raise awareness, generate qualified leads, and grow direct and channel sales. The Marketing Manager will develop and manage programs and content that will generate qualified enterprise sales leads and enable our growing network of Value Added Resellers and our direct sales team to gain a competitive advantage, convey value and close business.</p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;\">Summary: </strong>This position is an opportunity to grow your career by working at a disruptive technology startup, developing your skills in enterprise software marketing, and accelerating our growth.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Location: </strong>San Jose, California</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reports to:</strong> Director of Product Marketing</p>\r\n<p>Interested? Email a resume in reverse chronological format to <a href=\"mailto:marketing-jobs@vistarait.com\">marketing-jobs@vistarait.com</a>. Principals only.<a href=\"mailto:sales@vistarait.com\">\r\n</a></p>\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Analyzing competing products and positioning our product against them.</li>\r\n	<li>Writing original marketing materials such as PowerPoint presentations, product data sheets, solution briefs, web pages, white papers, blog posts, press releases, scripts and outlines for videos and animations, and tweets in American English.</li>\r\n	<li>Managing social media marketing channels such as our Twitter feed, blog, Facebook page, and YouTube channel.</li>\r\n	<li>Editing contents of web pages using WordPress.</li>\r\n	<li>Providing support to our internal customers in sales and external VAR, MSP, and OEM partners.</li>\r\n	<li>Managing internal and external resources to complete projects such as product launch promotions, web site enhancements, promotional campaigns, webinars and events taking place in the United States, and more.</li>\r\n	<li>Manage external contractors customizing our WordPress-powered web site and external designers creating imagery for it.</li>\r\n	<li>Developing content, events, and promotions to generate qualified enterprise sales leads.</li>\r\n	<li>Promoting and managing Internet-based events such as webinars and analyzing their effectiveness using tools like GoToWebinar, WebEx, and Google Analytics.</li>\r\n	<li>Managing trade show event appearances.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Experience and Required Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Mandatory: </strong>1-2 years of previous industry experience working in one or more of the following areas or at companies doing business one or more of the following areas: IT operations management; IT operations monitoring and management software solutions; network operations; network management; virtualization; storage, network, or computing solutions; data center management; cloud computing services or solutions; cloud management services or solutions</li>\r\n	<li>1-2 years of previous work experience in marketing. Relevant work experience would include enterprise, product, field, solution, or event marketing or marketing communications.</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to write high-quality customer-ready marketing materials. All applicants will be required to complete an in-person writing exercise to demonstrate their writing ability.</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent analytical ability and attention to detail.</li>\r\n	<li>Passion for rapid execution and delivering quality results quickly.</li>\r\n	<li>Strong project management skills are a must. Ability to define a desired business outcome, quickly develop a plan, and execute with minimal oversight to achieve desired outcome.</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to manage internal staff and external contractors cross-functionally.</li>\r\n	<li>Strong skills in using Microsoft Office suite and online collaboration solutions such as Google Docs.</li>\r\n	<li>Some flexibility in work hours to enable communication with staff and partners in other time zones and holding conference calls with India-based staff.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>Additional qualifications (not required, but desirable):</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;\">Experience editing and/or managing WordPress-powered web sites.</span></li>\r\n	<li>Experience with search engine optimizing web content.</li>\r\n	<li>Experience using SalesForce.com, HubSpot, GoToWebinar, WebEx, Google Analytics, and other online marketing tools.</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size: 