arait.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/vslide-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3000,1,'2014-04-12 06:15:20','2014-04-12 06:15:20','<section class=\"section\">\r\n<div class=\"container static-content\">\r\n<h1>Unified IT Operations Management for Modern IT</h1>\r\n<div style=\"-webkit-border-radius: 10px; -moz-border-radius: 10px;border-radius: 10px;  width: 300px; background: #F0F0F0; margin: 50px 80px; float: left; padding: 10px 15px;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center; margin:0; \">Download your free copy of our Unified IT Operations Management for Modern IT&nbsp;solution brief</h2>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center; padding: 20px 0; margin:0; \"><a href=\"http://v1.vistarait.com/?attachment_id=3801\"><img width=\"119\" height=\"155\" src=\"http://v1.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/unified-it-thumb.png\" alt=\"download\" style=\"box-shadow: 0 0 0 0; margin: 0 auto;\" class=\"size-full wp-image-2975 aligncenter\"></a></h2>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center; margin:0; \"><a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/unified-IT-operations-management-with-vistara-solution-brief.pdf\" download>Click here to download PDF</a></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>','Unified IT Operations Management for Modern IT','','publish','open','open','','unified-it-operations-management-thanks','','','2014-04-12 06:32:07','2014-04-12 06:32:07','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?page_id=3000',0,'page','',0),(3016,1,'2014-04-12 06:30:12','2014-04-12 06:30:12','','unified-IT-operations-management-with-vistara-solution-brief','','inherit','open','open','','unified-it-operations-management-with-vistara-solution-brief','','','2014-04-12 06:30:12','2014-04-12 06:30:12','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/unified-IT-operations-management-with-vistara-solution-brief.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(3023,1,'2014-04-12 06:55:02','2014-04-12 06:55:02','','tickyes','','inherit','open','open','','tickyes','','','2014-04-12 06:55:02','2014-04-12 06:55:02','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/tickyes.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3030,1,'2014-04-12 07:07:21','2014-04-12 07:07:21',' ','','','publish','open','open','','3030','','','2014-11-03 12:10:27','2014-11-03 12:10:27','',93,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=3030',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(3033,1,'2014-04-14 06:33:19','2014-04-14 06:33:19','<section class=\"section\">\r\n<div class=\"container static-content\">\r\n<h1>Managing Cisco Unified Computing System (UCS) with Vistara</h1>\r\n<p>Cisco Unified Computing System™ (UCS) is a next generation hardware infrastructure platform shaping data centers today. It ties computing, networking, storage access, and virtualization into a cohesive system to accelerate the delivery of new services to customers.</p>\r\n<p>Although UCS delivers many benefits through consolidation and unification, it poses significant challenges to customers in its varied requirements for monitoring and management. UCS environments are typically heterogeneous and run large numbers of applications with extensive volumes of data. Even though the UCS manager provides management capabilities to all UCS components, there are still management tasks such as cross system management, OS management, and application management which are out of its scope. Administrators typically use disparate tools to manage these assets and face major challenges in doing so.</p>\r\n<h2>Automatic Device Discovery for Cisco UCS</h2>\r\n<p>Vistara automatically discovers all the components of the UCS infrastructure from the blades right up to virtual machines hosted on the hypervisor. All the components are logically and hierarchically grouped in Vistara’s browser based user interface making it easy to navigate through the infrastructure. This helps the network operating center administrators to easily understand inter-component dependencies and to perform root cause and impact analysis when a problem occurs.</p>\r\n<h2>Integrated Monitoring and Management</h2>\r\n<p>Vistara monitors and manages numerous components of the UCS chassis. It uses SNMP and syslog to integrate with Cisco UCS APIs to collect information from the UCS manager. Standard monitors are listed below.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Monitored Components:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Chassis</li>\r\n	<li>Chassis fan module</li>\r\n	<li>Chassis fans</li>\r\n	<li>Power supply units</li>\r\n	<li>IO modules</li>\r\n	<li>Blade servers</li>\r\n	<li>Blade server adaptor units</li>\r\n	<li>Blade server memory arrays</li>\r\n	<li>Blade server processors</li>\r\n	<li>Fabric interconnect fans</li>\r\n	<li>Fabric interconnect power supplies</li>\r\n	<li>Fabric interconnect IO modules and Ethernet ports</li>\r\n	<li>Fabric interconnect IO module fiber channel ports</li>\r\n	<li>Fabric interconnect local storage and dynamic counters</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>UCS Hardware Status Monitoring:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Operational status for fans, LEDs, cards, and memory</li>\r\n	<li>Fault Condition: UCS error IDs, condition codes, rules, severity</li>\r\n	<li>Physical switch I/O operational and administrative status</li>\r\n	<li>UCS 6100 chassis management controller statistics</li>\r\n	<li>CPU statistics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>UCS Environmental Status Monitoring:</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"background: none;\">\r\n	<li>Power status for all components</li>\r\n	<li>UCS 6100 cooling fan type and condition</li>\r\n	<li>Temperature statistics on all components</li>\r\n	<li>Voltage status for each component</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>UCS Hardware Inventory:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Model revision, serial number, and vendor details for each chassis</li>\r\n	<li>Chassis ID, slot ID, model, revision, serial number, and vendor details for each blade</li>\r\n	<li>Switch ID, slot ID, model, revision, serial number, and vendor details for each fabric interconnect</li>\r\n	<li>Chassis ID, model, revision, serial number, and vendor details for each fabric extender</li>\r\n	<li>Chassis ID, model, revision, serial number, and vendor details for each network adaptor</li>\r\n	<li>Number of chassis installed</li>\r\n	<li>Number of servers per chassis</li>\r\n	<li>Memory available on each server</li>\r\n	<li>Type and quantity of interface cards one each server</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Virtual Environment Monitoring:</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"background: none;\">\r\n	<li>Server availability</li>\r\n	<li>Server performance: CPU, memory, disk</li>\r\n	<li>Server hardware monitoring</li>\r\n	<li>Network interface: total bytes/sec</li>\r\n	<li>Network interface: packets outbound errors</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Hosted Application Monitoring:</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"background: none;\">\r\n	<li>Application availability</li>\r\n	<li>Other application specific parameters</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Cisco UCS Health Checks</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Vistara enables administrators to easily conduct periodic health checks and best practice checks on the UCS environment. Standard supported checks include:</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"background: none;\">\r\n	<li>Software and firmware upgrades, ensuring optimal service levels for applications hosted within the Cisco UCS environment</li>\r\n	<li>Trend analysis on key performance data</li>\r\n	<li>Configuration backup checks to prepare for disaster recovery.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This ensures optimal service levels for applications while meeting performance requirements of underlying infrastructure and applications.</p>\r\n<h2>Secure Monitoring and Management to Support Compliance</h2>\r\n<p>Vistara monitoring is performed via the Vistara Gateway (VG) which provides all of the technology needed to deliver professional managed services. The Vistara Gateway controls and manages access to Cisco UCS and other devices via role based access control. Restricted access is provided to remediate any issue. All login sessions are recorded and attached to trouble tickets, meeting accountability and compliance requirements for IT operations.</p>\r\n<h2>Unified Monitoring and Management Across Multiple Devices on Physical and Virtual Infrastructure</h2>\r\n<p>Vistara unifies management of UCS with other components in your data center. All hardware components including UCS blades, network adaptor, storage and fabric interconnects, as well as other non-Cisco components such as fabric switches, storage, and network are laid out in a single view giving a complete picture of your data center. With extensive support for virtualization, Vistara provides the NOC team with complete information about all your hypervisors, guest virtual machines, and the application running on each of them. Vistara supplements the UCS manager to provide cross system and heterogeneous device management via a single pane of glass.</p>\r\n<h2>Benefit from Secure Remote Monitoring and Management Services</h2>\r\n<p>Vistara customers have the option of choosing secure remote monitoring and management services from NetEnrich or other Vistara partners. Customers can supplement their internal IT staff with additional remote staff to handle routing maintenance tasks and provide around the clock monitoring and management.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Supported UCS Components</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cisco UCS Blade Servers: B200, 230, 250 and 400 series blade servers</li>\r\n	<li>Cisco UCS Blade Server Chassis: Cisco UCS 5100 Series Blade Server Chassis</li>\r\n	<li>Cisco UCS C-Series Rack-Mount Servers</li>\r\n	<li>Cisco UCS C-Series Network Adapters</li>\r\n	<li>UCS Fabric Interconnects: Cisco 6000 Series Fabric Interconnects</li>\r\n	<li>UCS Fabric Extender: Cisco 2100 Series Fabric Extender</li>\r\n	<li>Cisco UCS Manager</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><!--MMS Cisco UCS-Datasheet-v031512.pdf - Cisco UCS datasheet (781 KB) Roycey Cheeran, 02/04/2013 09:21 pm Lifecycle Services-Cisco UCS-Datasheet-EC.docx - Lifecycle services Cisco UCS Datasheet (2.39 MB) Roycey Cheeran, 02/04/2013 09:37 pm CISCO UCS - EES MANAGE SOS.docx (165 KB) Eric Krock, 02/05/2013 02:17 pm--></p>\r\n<h2><a style=\"font-size: 13px;\" href=\"http://info.vistarait.com/vistara-contact-us\">Contact us</a><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\"> to request a demo and see for yourself!</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>','Cisco UCS','','publish','open','open','','cisco-ucs','','','2014-04-23 10:26:40','2014-04-23 10:26:40','',1664,'http://www.vistarait.com/?page_id=3033',0,'page','',0),(3035,1,'2014-04-14 06:48:55','2014-04-14 06:48:55','<section class=\"section\">\r\n<div class=\"container static-content\">\r\n<h1>Manage EMC VNX and VNXe with Vistara</h1>\r\n<p>Customers using EMC VNX and VNXe to build a private cloud can use Vistara as a single tool to manage unified storage solutions as well as the rest of their distributed IT infrastructure, including network devices, servers, virtual machines, and private clouds, public clouds, and hybrid clouds. EMC Labs has validated Vistara for unifying VNX and VNXe unified storage platforms with the rest of your IT infrastructure.</p>\r\n<div class=\"row devops-box dark-box\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\r\n<h3>Vistara and VNX / VNXe</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-9\">\r\n<p>VNX and VNXe are flexible data storage assets that are a perfect fit for creating a private cloud. Vistara is a complete SaaS IT lifecycle management platform. Vistara integrates VNX and VNXe APIs into the management of the overall IT infrastructure. Vistara unifies management of VNX and VNXe with the rest of your cloud. Vistara enables you to view and manage VNX, VNXe, and all of the other elements of your IT operation from within a single user interface.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-3\"><img class=\"wp-image-1011 alignright\" alt=\"EMC-VSPEX-Labs-Validated-250\" src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/EMC-VSPEX-Labs-Validated-250.jpg\" width=\"89\" height=\"110\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row devops-box dark-box\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\r\n<h3>Features</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-9\">\r\n<p>Vistara is a complete management package that not only automates management of internal and external cloud services at a high level, but also provides element management at the most detailed level. Vistara manages VNX and VNXe with features like these:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Storage pool monitoring</li>\r\n	<li>NFS mount publishing</li>\r\n	<li>Disk availability</li>\r\n	<li>Volume utilization</li>\r\n	<li>LUN publishing</li>\r\n	<li>Storage performance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-3\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3040\" alt=\"EMC VNX\" src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/EMC-VNX.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"400\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-9\">\r\n<p>Vistara gives you the big picture with lifecycle components including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Agentless management</li>\r\n	<li>Secure session recording</li>\r\n	<li>Change audit</li>\r\n	<li>Application correlation</li>\r\n	<li>Guest host to ESX correlation</li>\r\n	<li>Network mapping</li>\r\n	<li>Server mapping</li>\r\n	<li>Automated reporting</li>\r\n	<li>Automated incident ticketing</li>\r\n	<li>Role based access control</li>\r\n	<li>Time based access control</li>\r\n	<li>Business facing, automated service catalog</li>\r\n	<li>External cloud provisioning</li>\r\n	<li>VNX and VNXe private cloud provisioning</li>\r\n	<li>Federated cloud management</li>\r\n	<li>Change approval</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-3\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3041\" alt=\"EMC VNX\" src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/EMC-VNX1.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"710\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>','EMC VNX','','publish','open','open','','emc-vnx-vnxe-monitoring-management','','','2014-04-14 09:47:58','2014-04-14 09:47:58','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?page_id=3035',0,'page','',0),(3039,1,'2014-04-14 06:56:08','2014-04-14 06:56:08','','','','inherit','open','open','','emc-vspex-labs-validated-250-3','','','2014-04-14 06:56:08','2014-04-1