.js',0,'attachment','application/javascript',0),(3399,31,'2014-04-27 06:07:27','2014-04-27 06:07:27','','Vistara named Gartner Cool Vendor for IT Operations','','inherit','open','open','','cool-vendor-news','','','2014-04-27 06:07:27','2014-04-27 06:07:27','',3258,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Cool-Vendor-News.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3403,1,'2014-05-01 14:00:58','2014-05-01 14:00:58','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-3404\" alt=\"Promedia Keeps New Jersey School Districts Ahead of the Curve\" src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Promedia-Blog-Post.png\" width=\"250\" height=\"68\" />\r\n<p>When the security camera that watched over the back door at one of Ramsey School District’s schools went offline, techs at <a href=\"http://www.promedianj.com/\">Promedia</a> immediately notified the principal to make sure that the entrance was secured. The camera is part of the technology infrastructure that Promedia manages for the New Jersey school district, using Vistara for their IT operations management platform. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>School districts face pressure to provide next generation curricula and learning environments, meet changing regulations, keep their students secure, and all the while do more with less. Promedia is a leader in enabling K-12 education customers to solve their biggest challenges through technology. In a rapidly changing technology landscape, New Jersey school districts look to Promedia to provide guidance on how they can keep up with state initiatives to gear up for online testing, secure their schools in the physical and virtual world, and integrate technology with curriculum to bring 21st century classrooms to life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a technology solutions provider, Promedia will guide education customers end-to-end. After building technology roadmaps that help school districts select the right technology for their objectives, Promedia supports ERATE applications and grant proposals, installs the solution, serves as the on-site resource for contracted customer, and manages the technology through the lifecycle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Promedia has seen a shift as schools realize that they need to operate “like a business” to meet their education needs in an efficient and cost-effective way. Promedia has deployed the VSPEX architecture, including EMC VNXe unified storage, Cisco UCS servers and networking, and VMware vSphere virtualization. Redundancy and centralized data center solutions are no longer just for corporate IT. Schools need to be in compliance with new regulations for archiving, and physical security is creating new requirements to store the enormous video files that school security cameras produce. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the case of Ramsey School District, Promedia deployed a physical surveillance system to supervise all of the entry points into the school premises. With an EMC VNXe storage physical security solution managed on the Vistara platform, Promedia engineers have full knowledge into the status of all of the elements that keep the school secure. The Vistara solution monitors all of the elements that are critical to the physical surveillance system and uses service maps to notify Promedia when there is an incident with any element that would affect the service. The alerts are automatically ticketed and the single pane of glass lets engineers control the elements from the Vistara portal regardless of whether it’s an EMC storage device, virtual machine, Cisco switch, or an application. Vistara patch and antivirus management capabilities make sure that their solution stays up to date on a regular basis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Promedia engineers use Vistara as the platform to manage no only physical security, but any infrastructure component, from wireless deployments to classroom collaboration solutions, for over thirty education customers. Vistara enables Promedia to see, control, automate and optimize the physical, virtual, cloud and application elements to make sure that schools are connected, compliant and secure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, online testing has made wireless capability critical. Students must be connected during standardized test periods. Imagine the impact of an Internet outage when you’re already facing the stress of taking a test! Schools need to know what’s connected where and who is bringing their own device. This requires robust wireless monitoring down to the device level to understand how much data each device is consuming. Vistara alerts Promedia engineers when there is a risk of oversubscription of an access point, which could cause an outage. With the knowledge of which devices are affecting bandwidth, engineers can troubleshoot real time and remotely.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Promedia stays responsive to customer needs by working closely with Vistara and EMC engineers. Kevin O’Connor, Director of Service Delivery at Promedia says, “The Vistara engineering team is very open to suggestions and able to work with us to improve the platform. Even if it’s not in our current wheelhouse, we can develop monitoring tools for new technologies as we find solutions that fit school needs.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As technology needs in K-12 education continue to evolve, Promedia can rely on partners like Vistara and EMC to provide responsive managed services and build the best-of-breed infrastructure for its customers.</p>','Promedia Keeps New Jersey School Districts Ahead of the Curve','','publish','open','open','','promedia-keeping-new-jersey-school-districts-ahead','','','2014-09-19 04:47:48','2014-09-19 04:47:48','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=3403',0,'post','',0),(3404,31,'2014-05-01 13:50:43','2014-05-01 13:50:43','','Promedia Keeps New Jersey School Districts Ahead of the Curve','','inherit','open','open','','promedia-blog-post','','','2014-05-01 13:50:43','2014-05-01 13:50:43','',3403,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Promedia-Blog-Post.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3405,31,'2014-05-01 13:55:11','2014-05-01 13:55:11','','Promedia Keeps New Jersey School Districts Ahead of the Curve','','inherit','open','open','','promedia-blog-feed','','','2014-05-01 13:55:11','2014-05-01 13:55:11','',3403,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Promedia-Blog-Feed.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3410,31,'2014-05-03 06:29:24','2014-05-03 06:29:24',' ','','','publish','open','open','','3410','','','2015-04-29 11:15:20','2015-04-29 11:15:20','',8,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=3410',9,'nav_menu_item','',0),(3418,42,'2014-05-05 10:13:10','2014-05-05 10:13:10','<p><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-3432\" alt=\"EMC VPSEX MVP Award\" src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/EMC-VPSEX-MVP-Award-Blog-Post.jpg\" width=\"168\" height=\"224\" /></p>\r\n<p>Vistara is proud to announce that it has been awarded the <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/company/news/vistara-wins-vspex-valuable-player-award-emc-world-2014/\">2014 EMC Technology Connect MVP award</a>. Vistara is being recognized as an outstanding EMC partner for ensuring that VSPEX is positioned as the Infrastructure platform of choice for speeding cloud deployments. Check out our <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/company/news/vistara-wins-vspex-valuable-player-award-emc-world-2014/\">news release</a> for full details.</p>\r\n<p>Are you at EMC World? If so, drop by the Vistara booth (New Innovator area at Booth #830) and see a Vistara demo!</p>','Vistara Wins VSPEX Most Valuable Player Award at EMC World 2014','','publish','open','open','','vistara-wins-vspex-valuable-player-award-emc-world-2014','','','2014-09-19 04:48:12','2014-09-19 04:48:12','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=3418',0,'post','',0),(3421,31,'2014-05-06 04:43:56','2014-05-06 04:43:56','<section id=\"inner-spotlight-new\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">[shortmenu menu=\"who-we-are\" enhance=\"true\" arrow=\"false\"]</div>\r\n</section><section class=\"section\">\r\n<div class=\"container static-content new-news\" id=\"news-page\">\r\n<div class=\"press-left\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<h1>Press Release</h1>\r\n<div class=\"release-wrap\">\r\n<h2 class=\"name\">Vistara Wins VSPEX Most Valuable Player Award at EMC World 2014</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>IT operations management innovator recognized for delivering a best-in-class unified management solution </em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>LAS VEGAS, Nevada, May 7, 2014</b></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Vistara, innovator of a comprehensive SaaS solution for modern IT operations, today announced that it has been awarded the 2014 EMC® Technology Connect VSPEX MVP Award. Vistara delivers a best-in-class unified management solution for VSPEX® technology that provides advanced features over the native tools available. Vistara is one of only three EMC Technology Connect partners across the globe to have been recognized as a Most Valuable Player as part of the inaugural 2014 Technology Connect awards.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As the first SaaS-based IT operations management solution validated by EMC Labs for managing VSPEX, Vistara helps customers quickly provision and manage their VSPEX converged infrastructure solution by unifying service delivery across all elements of their IT infrastructure. Vistara is being recognized as an outstanding EMC partner for ensuring that VSPEX is positioned as the Infrastructure platform of choice for speeding cloud deployments.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>“We are proud to be recognized by EMC as a Most Valuable Player for VSPEX proven infrastructure,” said Varma Kunaparaju, Chief Technology Officer for Vistara. “Customers adopt converged infrastructure solutions such as EMC VSPEX, because it provides them with the ability to quickly bolster the infrastructure behind private and public clouds. What Vistara brings to the table is a comprehensive platform for key IT Operations management functions within a single intuitive dashboard. We empower VSPEX customers with hybrid deployments to centralize the management and governance across internal and external clouds. ”</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Gary Garcia, Director of Global Solutions Marketing for EMC VSPEX said, “EMC is pleased to recognize Vistara’s achievements with our Technology Connect VSPEX MVP award. Vistara provides holistic VSPEX management capabilities with on-demand end-of-month reporting to simplify charge back and help businesses get the best return on their investment. Working with EMC and Vistara, customers can attain greater freedom and control as they deploy and manage their public, private, and hybrid clouds.”</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>“It is a privilege for Vistara to be chosen from the many partner offerings in the EMC Technology Connect program and acknowledged for developing customer-centric solutions for unified cloud management,” adds Kunaparaju. “We look forward to continuing our strong engagement with the EMC team and VSPEX channel partners to meet the growing needs of enterprises for cloud infrastructure management.”</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To learn more about Vistara’s IT platform visit <a title=\"Vistara Home Page\" href=\"http://www.vistarait.com\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.vistarait.com</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Follow Vistara at <a title=\"Vistara Blog\" href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/blog/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.vistarait.com/blog/</a>; on Twitter at <a title=\"Twitter @VistaraIT\" href=\"https://twitter.com/VistaraIT\" target=\"_blank\">@VistaraIT</a>; and on Facebook at <a title=\"Vistara at Facebook\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/VistaraIT\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/VistaraIT</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>About Vistara</strong></p>\r\n<p>Vistara is an Advantage partner in the EMC Business Partner Program for Technology Connect Partners. The company provides a comprehensive SaaS solution for modern IT operations that is currently used by over 1000 customers. Vistara automatically discovers a customer’s entire distributed IT infrastructure and enables customers to unify IT operations management, manage public and private clouds, and deliver self-service IT. Headquartered in San Jose, Calif., Vistara sells directly and through our network of leading distributors and value added resellers. Vistara’s technology partners include some of the largest software and hardware vendors worldwide. To learn more about Vistara, visit <a title=\"Vistara Home Page\" href=\"http://www.vistarait.com\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.vistarait.com</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"># # #</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>EMC and VSPEX are registered trademarks or trademarks or trademarks of EMC Corporation in the United States and other countries. All other trademarks used herein are the property of their respective owners. © Copyright 2014 EMC Corporation. All rights reserved. </em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"press-right\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"widget-wrap\">\r\n<h3>Share this page</h3>\r\n<div class=\"widget-inner social-inner\">[ssba]</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"widget-wrap\">\r\n<h3>Media Contact</h3>\r\n<div class=\"widget-inner\">\r\n<strong>Kevin Wolf</strong>\r\n<p>(650) 327-1641<br>\r\nkevin@tgprllc.com</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>','Vistara Wins VSPEX Most Valuable Player Award at EMC World 2014','','publish','open','open','','vistara-wins-vspex-valuable-player-award-emc-world-2014','','','2016-09-28 12:39:58','2016-09-28 12:39:58','',1383,'http://www.vistarait.com/?page_id=3421',0,'page','',0),(3432,31,'2014-05-07 05:12:32','2014-05-07 05:12:32','','EMC VPSEX MVP Award','','inherit','open','open','','emc-vpsex-mvp-award-blog-post','','','2014-05-07 05:12:32','2014-05-07 05:12:32','',3418,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/EMC-VPSEX-MVP-Award-Blog-Post.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3434,31,'2014-05-07 05:13:42','2014-05-07 05:13:42','','EMC VPSEX MVP Award','','inherit','open','open','','emc-vpsex-mvp-award-blog-feed','','','2014-05-07 05:13:42','2014-05-07 05:13:42','',3418,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/EMC-VPSEX-MVP-Award-Blog-Feed.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3456,1,'2014-05-08 13:46:00','2014-05-08 13:46:00','<p>Huge thanks to attendees, partners, and EMC for a fantastic EMC World 2014!</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Collage-11.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-3509\" title=\"Vistara Photos from EMC World 2014\" alt=\"Vistara Photos from EMC World 2014\" src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Collage-11.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"349\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Vistara hit the ground running as a New Innovator Sponsor in Las Vegas last week. Here are some highlights...</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b>Vistara Wins VSPEX MVP</b> - We are honored to be one of three EMC Technology Connect partners across the globe to be recognized in the inaugural awards. Read more about our <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/company/news/vistara-wins-vspex-valuable-player-award-emc-world-2014/\" target=\"_blank\">MVP Award</a>.</li>\r\n	<li><b>What Matters Most in IT Ops</b> - Thanks to those who participated in our very scientific poll to find out what is most important to YOU in IT operations. We had great discussions and debates about the relative importance of automation versus reporting, and what \"single pane of glass\" and \"first to know\" mean to different organizations. The common thread was that there are opportunities for improvement across the board. And the survey says...\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/it-operations-management-survey.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-3517\" title=\"IT Operation Management Survey Results\" alt=\"IT Operation Management Survey Results\" src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/it-operations-management-survey.jpg\" width=\"448\" height=\"280\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>\"Automation\" came out on top, followed by \"Reporting\". \"First to know\" and \"Single pane of glass\" tied for third. <i>Disclaimer: Results may be biased by health conscious voters and post-lunch visitors who chose to vote instead of eating their Skittles!</i></p></li>\r\n	<li><b>VSPEX Assembly Line</b> - Vistara represented the VSPEX ecosystem in the Partner Lounge VSPEX Assembly Line where EMC and partners demonstrated to channel partners how to Engage, Design, Build, Provision, and Deploy VSPEX. Congratulations to MTM, who won the VSPEX Assembly Line Sweepstakes, including one year of Vistara! Learn more about what <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Vistara-and-VSPEX-AAG.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Vistara and VSPEX</a> can do for you.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Vistara CTO on theCUBE</b> - We were excited to see Vistara CTO Varma Kunaparaju on live streaming as he was interviewed by Jeff Frick and Stu Miniman on theCUBE. See <a href=\"http://youtu.be/2795Kjvpxnk\" target=\"_blank\">Varma\'s segment</a> to learn about Vistara\'s vision and how to manage converged infrastructure with Vistara as IT infrastructure and service personnel become federated.</li>\r\n	<li><b>VSPEX and Brocade</b> - Thanks to Brocade for a great partnership and letting us share Vistara\'s capabilities across the VSPEX ecosystem. You may have seen Vistara at Brocade\'s booth demoing <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JML5T6iLbSQ\" target=\"_blank\">how to manage VSPEX with Vistara</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Thanks again for your engagement at EMC World 2014! We look forward to next year!</p>','A Great EMC World 2014','','publish','open','open','','great-emc-world-2014','','','2014-09-19 04:48:35','2014-09-19 04:48:35','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=3456',0,'post','',0),(3460,36,'2014-05-12 04:35:09','2014-05-12 04:35:09','','Slider-3-BG','','inherit','open','open','','slider-3-bg','','','2014-05-12 04:35:09','2014-05-12 04:35:09','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Slider-3-BG.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3463,36,'2014-05-12 04:55:11','2014-05-12 04:55:11','','Video player','','inherit','open','open','','video-player-2','','','2014-05-12 04:55:11','2014-05-12 04:55:11','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Video-player1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3489,36,'2014-05-12 12:45:07','2014-05-12 12:45:07','','lmbtn','','inherit','open','open','','lmbtn','','','2014-05-12 12:45:07','2014-05-12 12:45:07','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/lmbtn.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3495,1,'2014-05-12 21:34:44','2014-05-12 21:34:44','Vistara delivers a best-in-class unified management solution for VSPEX technology that provides advanced features over the native tools available.','Vistara and VSPEX At A Glance','Manage EMC VSPEX Proven Infrastructure Solutions with Vistara','inherit','open','open','','vistara-and-vspex-aag','','','2014-05-12 21:34:44','2014-05-12 21:34:44','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Vistara-and-VSPEX-AAG.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(3509,36,'2014-05-13 14:05:18','2014-05-13 14:05:18','','A Great EMC World 2014','','inherit','open','open','','collage-1-2','','','2014-05-13 14:05:18','2014-05-13 14:05:18','',3456,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Collage-11.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3517,1,'2014-05-13 21:36:29','2014-05-13 21:36:29','','it-operations-management-survey','','inherit','open','open','','it-operations-management-survey','','','2014-05-13 21:36:29','2014-05-13 21:36:29','',3456,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/it-operations-management-survey.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3524,31,'2014-05-14 04:49:17','2014-05-14 04:49:17','','What Matters Most in IT Operations','','inherit','open','open','','what-matters-most-in-it-operations-blog-feed','','','2014-05-14 04:49:17','2014-05-14 04:49:17','',3456,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/What-Matters-Most-in-IT-Operations-Blog-Feed.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3529,36,'2014-05-14 06:23:34','2014-05-14 06:23:34','','187px-RedHat.svg','','inherit','open','open','','187px-redhat-svg','','','2014-05-14 06:23:34','2014-05-14 06:23:34','',1122,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/187px-RedHat.svg_.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3537,31,'2014-05-15 12:51:47','2014-05-15 12:51:47','','Vistara Cloud Essentials - AAG','','inherit','open','open','','vistara-cloud-essentials-aag','','','2014-05-15 12:51:47','2014-05-15 12:51:47','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Vistara-Cloud-Essentials-AAG.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(3541,1,'2014-05-17 00:49:58','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Vistara is pleased to announce the availability of Vistara 3.5, which includes the following new enhancements:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#element-monitoring-snmp-trap-exclusion-ip-address\">Improved Element Monitoring with SNMP Trap Exclusion by IP Address</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#reporting-element-count-trend-availability-server-capacity\">Improved Reporting for Element Counts, Trends, Availability, and Server Capacity</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#customizable-hardware-report\">Customizable Hardware Report</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#user-report\">User Report</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 id=\"element-monitoring-snmp-trap-exclusion-ip-address\">Improved Element Monitoring with SNMP Trap Exclusion by IP Address</h2>\r\nVistara now supports the ability to exclude SNMP traps from specific IP addresses to enable IT administrators to avoid duplication in monitoring. In large environments, many devices have multiple IP addresses, and SNMP traps may be generated from every IP address. In such environments, IP addresses of interest must be identified iteratively, starting with traps from all devices and narrowing down to IP addresses of interest through exclusion of duplicate IP addresses. Vistara already supported including specified IP address ranges and now enables exclusion of IP addresses for SNMP trap processing as well.\r\n<h2 id=\"reporting-element-count-trend-availability-server-capacity\">Improved Reporting for Element Counts, Trends, Availability, and Server Capacity</h2>\r\nVistara\'s Customer Executive Report provides a convenient summary of key performance indicators as a fully formatted PowerPoint or PDF presentation that\'s ready to share with executive stakeholders. The Customer Executive Report has been enhanced to provide IT managers and executives an even more comprehensive picture of operational health. Enhancements to the report include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Element Count Trend and Graph:</span> Shows a graph with the trend of the number of elements under management.</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Element Mix Percentage:</span> Shows a pie chart with the percentage of elements in your managed infrastructure by device type.</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Availability Trend and Distribution:</span> Provides granular details of availability including trends, graphs and number of devices that went down with their downtime, aggregated at the level of the device type.</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Server Capacity:</span> Provides average CPU and memory utilization numbers with graphs.</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">New Elements Added Under Management:</span> See the new elements placed under management during the time period of your choosing so you can measure your progress towards achieving unified management of your IT infrastructure and operations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 id=\"customizable-hardware-report\">Customizable Hardware Report</h2>\r\nThe new Hardware Report is now multi-faceted with individual sub-reports covering specific areas such as servers, workstations, disks, and network devices. You can also create custom report templates to generate reports with any combination of the following types of information:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Disk Inventory</li>\r\n	<li>Network Device Inventory</li>\r\n	<li>Server and Workstation Inventory</li>\r\n	<li>Device Inventory by Discovered, Managed, Unmanaged, and Agent Installed Status</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 id=\"user-report\">User Report</h2>\r\nThe User Report provides a snapshot of successful and failed logins by user account, IP addresses of successful and failed login attempts, and the current status of user accounts (active or disabled). This helps IT administrators detect hostile login attempts as well as recognize when users have innocently locked themselves out through multiple failed login attempts.\r\n<h2>Unified Monitoring and Reporting for Unified IT Operations Management</h2>\r\nVistara\'s robust element monitoring and reporting capabilities provide a solid foundation for unified IT operations management. Vistara services as a trusted single source of truth for IT operations professionals. <a href=\"http://info.vistarait.com/vistara-contact-us\">Contact Vistara</a> to learn more today!','Now Available: Vistara 3.5 with Improved Element Monitoring and Custom Reporting','','draft','open','open','','vistara-3-5-snmp-element-monitoring-reporting','','','2014-05-17 00:49:58','2014-05-17 00:49:58','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=3541',0,'post','',0),(3551,1,'2014-05-16 22:41:31','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Vistara is pleased to announce the availability of Vistara 3.6, which includes the following new enhancements:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#emc-symmetrix-vmax-storage-solution-management\">EMC Symmetrix VMAX Storage Solution Management</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 id=\"emc-symmetrix-vmax-storage-solution-management\">EMC Symmetrix VMAX Storage Solution Management</h2>\r\nVistara now supports the EMC Symmetrix VMAX series of storage devices. Vistara provides a unified view into the status and performance of your VMAX array and manages the following components:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Engines, including Directors and Ports</li>\r\n	<li>Disks and RAID Groups:</li>\r\n	<li>Storage Pools: what are, capacity of each, capacity utilization</li>\r\n	<li>Volumes and LUNs</li>\r\n	<li>Hosts, Storage Gr