pg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3663,36,'2014-06-09 04:59:49','2014-06-09 04:59:49','','Read now','','inherit','open','open','','read-now-button','','','2014-06-09 04:59:49','2014-06-09 04:59:49','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Read-now-button.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3666,36,'2014-06-09 05:48:34','2014-06-09 05:48:34','Gartner 2014 CoolVendor','Gartner 2014 CoolVendor','','inherit','open','open','','badge','','','2014-06-09 05:48:34','2014-06-09 05:48:34','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Badge.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3668,36,'2014-06-10 06:29:11','2014-06-10 06:29:11','','Ratna Gudlavalleti ','','inherit','open','open','','ratna','','','2014-06-10 06:29:11','2014-06-10 06:29:11','',669,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Ratna.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3686,36,'2014-06-11 07:35:42','2014-06-11 07:35:42','','Request a Free Demo','','inherit','open','open','','req-demo','','','2014-06-11 07:35:42','2014-06-11 07:35:42','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Req-demo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3691,1,'2014-06-12 21:49:13','2014-06-12 21:49:13','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-3695\" src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Vistara-Booth-at-Gartner-IOM.jpg\" alt=\"Vistara at Gartner IOM\" width=\"250\" height=\"182\" />\r\n<p>\r\nThis week was Gartner Infrastructure & Operations Management (IOM) Summit and its inaugural year to zoom in on the \"OM\" part of \"IOM,\" leaving behind its history as the \"other DC conference.\"</p>\r\n<p>\r\nVistara participated as a Silver Sponsor. We were thrilled to spend three days in lively discussions (also known as \"geeking out\") with Gartner analysts, end users, and industry peers on the challenges and opportunities to align IT infrastructure and services with organizational goals. Kudos to Gartner for bringing the fresh focus to the Summit!</p>\r\n<p>\r\nHere are some of our highlights from IOM:</p>\r\n<p><ul>\r\n	<li><p><b>Eddie Obeng and WAM...</b> Professor Eddie Obeng kicked off the Summit with a dynamic and interactive keynote, calling on leaders to proactively seek change and gave us tactics to combat the “heavy weight of inertia and tradition” to navigate transformation in organizations. Check out <a title=\"World After Midnight video from Gartner IOM Keynote\" href=\"http://youtu.be/yVIe1MOpiHU\" target=\"_blank\">his opening video</a>, well worth the 9 minutes if you missed it!</p></li>\r\n	<li><p><b>Bimodal IT...</b> Ronni Colville and Debra Curtis spoke about balancing the bimodal tension between renovating the IT core versus operating in nonlinear mode when you need speed, innovation, and can operate with high degrees of uncertainty. This theme of providing safe, reliable IT while delivering new value at digital speed permeated throughout the three days. Their Autobahn analogy totally resonated with us - stay tuned for more from Vistara about how we can be your Autobahn to let you safely fly at 120 mph!</p></li>\r\n<li><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-3700\" src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0231.jpg\" alt=\"Let Vistara see across your tools\" width=\"200\" height=\"150\" /><p><b>So many tools...</b> Jonah Kowall asked the audience during his unified monitoring session how many monitoring tools they used. A staggering 67% of attendees were using more than 6 monitoring tools, and 27% have more than 10 monitoring tools in their IT environment!</p> \r\n<p>We saw this theme of tool proliferation across ITOM disciplines and heard from many of you about the challenges this creates. We had great conversations about how Vistara\'s single pane of glass visibility can help unify your IT operations, whether you keep, rationalize, or replace these tools.</p></li>\r\n</ul></p>\r\n<p>Thanks to all for visiting us and engaging with Vistara. We had a blast and look forward to continuing the conversations! Can\'t wait for IOM 2015!</p>','Gartner IOM Summit 2014: Change, Renovation and Speed','','publish','open','open','','gartner-iom-summit_2014','','','2014-06-12 21:51:21','2014-06-12 21:51:21','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=3691',0,'post','',0),(3695,1,'2014-06-12 20:57:27','2014-06-12 20:57:27','','Vistara Booth at Gartner IOM','','inherit','open','open','','vistara-booth-at-gartner-iom','','','2014-06-12 20:57:27','2014-06-12 20:57:27','',3691,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Vistara-Booth-at-Gartner-IOM.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3700,1,'2014-06-12 21:23:31','2014-06-12 21:23:31','','Too many tools','Tool proliferation was a common theme across IOM','inherit','open','open','','img_0231','','','2014-06-12 21:23:31','2014-06-12 21:23:31','',3691,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0231.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3723,42,'2014-06-19 17:09:44','2014-06-19 17:09:44','<p>The federation of IT will change the IT operations management landscape for enterprise. Vistara\'s CTO, Varma Kunaparaju had a great discussion with hosts of <a href=\"http://siliconangle.tv/\" target=\"_blank\">theCube</a>, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/JeffFrick\" target=\"_blank\">Jeff Frick</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/stu\" target=\"_blank\">Stu Miniman</a>, about the key trends shaping enterprise IT and Vistara’s vision for IT operations management at <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/company/blog/great-emc-world-2014/\" target=\"_blank\">EMC World 2014</a> last month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first major shift is the \"federation of infrastructure\" where on-premise infrastructure and application workloads are migrating to private and public clouds. The second is the \"federation of resources\" where the personnel for managing the infrastructure are coming not just from internal IT but also from other internal functions, resellers, technology vendors, and service providers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Watch Varma discuss the federation of IT (starting at 7:53 minutes) and more on theCube!</p>\r\n\r