 Chairman<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/pub/raju-chekuri/1/31b/664\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/linkedin.jpg\" alt=\"LinkedIn\" /></a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/rajunetenrich\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/twitter-gray.png\" alt=\"Twitter\" /></a></p>\r\nRaju is Vistara’s Chairman and CEO. Raju co-founded Vistara when he recognized the transition by enterprise IT to a federated model and believed that there was a need for element management. He was instrumental in providing the leadership to spin out Vistara to focus exclusively on delivering a world class technology platform for modern IT. Raju has over 25 years of experience as an entrepreneur and leader in the Enterprise IT industry. Raju also founded NetEnrich, a pure-play provider of Remote IT Infrastructure Management Services (RIM) to enterprise clients of all sizes. Previously, Raju founded and led Velio Communications, Inc., a bleeding-edge network and systems semiconductor company funded by Sequoia Capital, Redpoint Ventures and Capital Research. Velio was purchased by LSI Logic and Rambus in 2003. Prior to Velio, Chekuri was Director of Strategic Ventures at Cadence Design Systems.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"team-member-box row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-2\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/varma.png\" alt=\"Varma Kunaparaju\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-10\">\r\n<p class=\"member-name\">Varma Kunaparaju | President and CTO<a href=\"https://twitter.com/@varma1\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/twitter-gray.png\" alt=\"Twitter\" /></a></p>\r\nVarma is President and Chief Technology Officer at Vistara. Varma co-founded Vistara, driving the development of the unified IT operations management platform. Varma has over 20 years of experience in high-technology engineering, and has a proven record of building and delivering enterprise software. Prior to Vistara, Kunaparaju was co-founder of NetEnrich. Previously, Varma was co-founder and Vice President of Product Development at NexPrise, where he was responsible for delivering six major versions of its products to Fortune 100 companies. Varma holds two patents in collaborative product development and co-developed BML, which was the first XML-based language for transporting collaborative application data over the internet.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"team-member-box row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-2\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/ratna.png\" alt=\"Ratna Gudlavalleti\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-10\">\r\n<p class=\"member-name\">Ratna Gudlavalleti | Senior Director, Engineering<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/ratnagudlavalleti\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/linkedin.jpg\" alt=\"LinkedIn\" /></a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/RatnaGudlavalle\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/twitter-gray.png\" alt=\"Twitter\" /></a></p>\r\nRatna leads engineering at Vistara. Previously, he was director of engineering at NetEnrich and held engineering roles at NexPrise, Wipro, and SE Technologies. He has a B.Tech in ECE from Andhra University and an M.Tech in Computer Science from Cochin University of Science and Technology.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"team-member-box row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-2\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/aki-naito.png\" alt=\"Aki Naito\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-10\">\r\n<p class=\"member-name\">Aki Naito | Senior Director, Marketing<a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/in/akinaito\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/linkedin.jpg\" alt=\"LinkedIn\" /></a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/akinaito\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/twitter-gray.png\" alt=\"Twitter\" /></a></p>\r\nAki leads marketing and communications at Vistara. Aki joined Vistara from Cisco Systems, where she drove joint marketing with service provider and cloud partners globally. Previously she focused on global industry marketing and marketing initiatives in Asia-Pacific at Cisco. Aki began her career as a business analyst at Spencer Stuart, a global executive search firm. Aki has an MBA from Stanford Graduate School of Business and a BA from Dartmouth College in Engineering Physics.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"team-member-box row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-2\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/mahesh.png\" alt=\"Mahesh Ramachandran\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-10\">\r\n<p class=\"member-name\">Mahesh Ramachandran | Senior Director, Product Management<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/ramachandranm\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/linkedin.jpg\" alt=\"LinkedIn\" /></a></p>\r\nMahesh leads product management at Vistara. Previously, Mahesh held leadership roles in product management at VMware, NetScout Systems, and Hewlett Packard. He has over 15 years of industry experience spanning IT management products for servers, networks, storage systems and applications. Mahesh holds a Bachelor’s and Master’s degrees from the University of California, Davis and a MBA degree from San Jose State University.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"team-member-box row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-2\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/denny.png\" alt=\"Denny Riley\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-10\">\r\n<p class=\"member-name\">Denny Riley | Vice President, Sales & Channels<a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/pub/denny-riley/0/110/50\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/linkedin.jpg\" alt=\"LinkedIn\" /></a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Caldriley\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/themes/twentythirteen/images/twitter-gray.png\" alt=\"Twitter\" /></a></p>\r\nDenny is responsible for driving the revenue growth of Vistara worldwide sales channels. He has over 25 years experience managing enterprise sales organizations comprising direct, inside, and channel teams. Prior to Vistara, Denny served as Vice President of Sales for a number of start-up companies as well as Vice President for EMC’s Infrastructure Software Channel where he was instrumental in building global relationships and expanding the company’s enterprise customer base. Denny holds a BA in Psychology and Education from Gustavus and Business Administration credentials from St. Thomas and IBM Financial Program out of Harvard.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>','Team','','publish','open','open','','team','','','2015-02-05 07:12:56','2015-02-05 07:12:56','',670,'http://www.vistarait.com/company/about-vistara-2/',0,'page','',0),(3802,36,'2014-07-03 06:53:57','2014-07-03 06:53:57','','Company','','publish','open','open','','about-vistara','','','2014-12-08 06:22:22','2014-12-08 06:22:22','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=3802',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(3804,36,'2014-07-03 07:14:15','2014-07-03 07:14:15',' ','','','publish','open','open','','3804','','','2014-12-08 06:22:22','2014-12-08 06:22:22','',670,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=3804',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(3809,36,'2014-07-03 08:39:41','2014-07-03 08:39:41','','windows-azure','','inherit','open','open','','windows-azure1','','','2014-07-03 08:39:41','2014-07-03 08:39:41','',96,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/windows-azure1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3810,36,'2014-07-03 08:43:41','2014-07-03 08:43:41','','Google Cloud Platform','','inherit','open','open','','gcplogo','','','2014-07-03 08:43:41','2014-07-03 08:43:41','',96,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/gcplogo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3813,36,'2014-07-03 09:22:22','2014-07-03 09:22:22','','casestudy icon','','inherit','open','open','','casestudy-icon-01','','','2014-07-03 09:22:22','2014-07-03 09:22:22','',349,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/casestudy-icon-01.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3814,36,'2014-07-03 09:31:47','2014-07-03 09:31:47','','Press release','','inherit','open','open','','pressrelease','','','2014-07-03 09:31:47','2014-07-03 09:31:47','',349,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/pressrelease.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3817,1,'2014-07-07 07:46:42','2014-07-07 07:46:42','<p> To manage the information growth caused by the nexus of forces (social, mobile, cloud and information), enterprises have deployed a heterogeneous range of storage devices from multiple vendors. Some of the challenges facing enterprises in optimizing storage management include:</p> \r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Each storage device comes with its own management console. Storage admins have been forced to use multiple tools for troubleshooting issues across heterogeneous storage elements resulting in operational delays in resolving critical incidents.</li> \r\n        <li>With specialized resources managing storage infrastructure, enterprises don\'t want these highly skilled employees spending time responding to every minor storage escalation.</li> \r\n        <li>Enterprises have deployed point tools that don\'t work well together and fail to deliver a unified view across storage infrastructure.</li> \r\n</ul>\r\n<p>IT teams looking to increase operational efficiencies and enhance business outcomes are deploying storage management solutions that can auto-discover storage devices across all major vendors and deliver a single source of truth for storage infrastructure. The new generation of storage management solutions can discover and quickly manage multiple storage devices from different vendors not only through API level integrations but also using Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP), Command-line Interface (CLI) and industry frameworks like Storage Management Initiative Specification (SMI-S). Enterprise management solutions like Vistara can collect device information during auto-discovery and then define the right monitors so that you can start improving service levels immediately.</p> \r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-3824\" src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Storage-Device-Dashboard-Blog-Post.png\" alt=\"Storage Device Dashboard\" width=\"600\" height=\"624\" /><p>Your IT operations solution should provide three categories of metrics for delivering enterprise storage management at scale:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b>Status Metrics</b> track availability of all the storage components in your organization. A storage system typically consists of physical components (arrays, disks, processors and ports) and logical components (domains, pools and volumes). Your enterprise storage management platform should monitor both physical and logical components for optimal storage performance. Storage elements also need <strong>supporting components</strong> like storage switches that deliver fast and reliable connectivity. The right solution will dynamically monitor supporting elements and deliver relevant alerts to ensure that your storage devices are accessible to hosts and end-users.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Capacity Metrics</b> monitor storage utilization across your enterprise. Your storage admins will be able to analyze disk consumption metrics so that business-critical applications don’t run out of disk space. If you\'ve adopted the concept of <b>thin provisioning</b> to increase the return on storage investments, your management solution will identify how much of virtual storage is over-subscribed and help you quickly decide if a host or user needs an upgrade.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Performance Metrics</b> detect how well your storage system is performing. Most tools deliver a basic set of performance metrics (IOPS, throughput and latency) for storage. With a modern IT operations solution, you can view metrics across multiple components (processors, ports, disks and pools) of the storage system. Tracking similar metrics across multiple components helps to accurately zero down on availability and performance trends and deliver proactive management for your storage elements. If a business user complains of not being able to access an application, admins can drill-down on the underlying components for identifying hot spots and taking corrective action.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Gartner has predicted that the increasingly heterogeneous storage environments will require a new set of “management and orchestration tools<sup>[1]</sup>.” Vistara delivers unified IT operations management across all of your elements and enables you monitor, alert and report across your storage environment within a single pane of glass. If you want to use Vistara to monitor the availability of individual physical and logical components of your storage infrastructure, <a href=\"http://info.vistarait.com/vistara-contact-us\">request a live demo today!</a></p> \r\n\r\n<p>[<a href=\"https://www.gartner.com/doc/2628421/tech-gotomarket-storage-providers-focus\">1</a>] Tech Go-to-Market: Storage Providers Should Focus on Three Growth Opportunities Through 2016, Jimmie Chang, et al. November 22, 2013 ,</p>','Enterprise Storage Management At Scale','','private','open','open','','enterprise-storage-management','','','2014-09-19 04:45:42','2014-09-19 04:45:42','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=3817',0,'post','',0),(3828,31,'2014-07-07 08:12:39','2014-07-07 08:12:39','','Storage Device Dashboard ','','inherit','open','open','','storage-device-dashboard-blog-post','','','2014-07-07 08:12:39','2014-07-07 08:12:39','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Storage-Device-Dashboard-Blog-Post.png',0,'attachme