t=\"Moving Up The Stack - Blog Post\" width=\"199\" height=\"266\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-4738\" />VARs are challenged to provide value to IT customers, stay on top of the latest technology, and keep their business profitable. To become a trusted advisor, you must offer state-of-the-art consultative services, provide value to earn recurring business, and expand your range of services to become a one-stop-shop for your client.\r\n<p>\r\nVARs have traditionally sold hardware and provided deployment, support and maintenance to add value on top of the OEMs. To stay relevant to customers, IT partners need to understand software, management, and cloud. So why move up the stack?\r\n<p><ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Market Opportunity</strong> - Cloud is here to stay. Gartner says end user spend on cloud will be $210B+ by 2016. Cloud based deployment (XaaS) reduces traditional deployment services, but creates new opportunity for XaaS deployment, migration, support and upsell.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Profitability</strong> - Software and services are higher margin businesses, and moving into these areas provide recurring revenue streams and higher customer lifetime value. Leveraging cloud consumption models reduce capex requirements.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Value To Customer</strong> - As a trusted advisor, partners need to provide visibility and insights into a client\'s infrastructure and be proactive. IT teams need their “context” to be managed so that they can focus on “core” activity to drive their business.</li>\r\n</ul><p>\r\nVistara participated at Avnet\'s VSPEX Assembly Line at the EMC Executive Briefing Center last week. Vistara is proud to be part of the VSPEX Ecosystem and of Avnet and EMC\'s initiative to enable partner organizations to discover, develop, and deliver VSPEX programs in an ever more productive and sustainable manner. Vistara offers partners a flexible IT operations management solution that provides \"choice\" as they manage heterogeneous client infrastructure and a platform to build a scalable managed service practice.\r\n<p>\r\nWhether it\'s providing a self-service platform for end users, managing your customers\' IT environment, or building and reselling cloud services, Vistara can help you evolve to sustain more predictable, managed growth and map your path up the stack to become the \"trusted advisor\" to your customers. \r\n<p>\r\nLearn more about how Vistara can help you <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/company/resources/presentations/transform-into-cloud-provider/\" title=\"transform your business\" target=\"_blank\">transform your business</a> and see how <a href=\"http://info.vistarait.com/webinar-managed-services-business\" title=\"DATACORP\" target=\"_blank\">DATACORP</a> did it with Vistara.','Moving Up The Stack','','publish','open','open','','moving-stack','','','2014-09-19 04:50:12','2014-09-19 04:50:12','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=4716',0,'post','',0),(4720,18,'2014-09-10 04:37:49','2014-09-10 04:37:49','We have released Vistara 3.7.0, with exciting new features including:<p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Knowledge Base</strong> for fully integrated knowledge management capability</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Remote Multi-Console Sessions</strong> that simplify the management of multiple identical devices</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Alert Management Enhancements</strong> including new reports, dashboard and alert detail screen updates</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><h2>Knowledge Base</h2></p>\r\n<p>We are excited to announce that Vistara now supports knowledge management via the new Knowledge Base feature. IT organizations can now create, share and maintain Knowledge Articles that represent commonly used information such as troubleshooting tips and standard operating procedures, fully integrated with the Vistara IT operations management platform.</p>\r\n<p>Knowledge Base organizes how-to articles across categories and associates this information with device groups and monitoring templates to help IT departments and business users quickly find information about their IT operations that is both current and accurate. IT teams can also create and share user generated content that addresses common IT problems and reduces the volume of support calls through self-service knowledge articles.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Knowledge-Base.png\" alt=\"Knowledge Base\" width=\"800\" height=\"623\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-4748\" style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\"/>\r\n\r\n<p><h2>Remote Multi-Console Sessions</h2></p>\r\nVistara now allows users to select multiple devices and launch remote consoles into these devices in a single action. Users can interact with multiple consoles from a single UI to broadcast the same command and run SCP File Transfer across multiple consoles.\r\n<p>\r\nAs more IT organizations embrace DevOps principles, the ability to manage, for example, a cluster of identical cloud instances, will further simplify the IT operations required to delivery agile development and continuous integration. To learn more about how Vistara is using our own technology to manage our highly distributed SaaS application, <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/company/resources/latestwebinars/?commid=125695\" title=\"join us on our next webinar\" target=\"_blank\">join us on our next webinar</a> on Sept 17!\r\n<p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Remote-Multi-Console-Sessions-Blog-Post.png\" alt=\"Remote Multi-Console Sessions\" width=\"1039\" height=\"600\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-4751\" style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\"/>\r\n<p><h2>Alert Management Enhancements</h2></p>\r\nWe\'ve updated a number of Vistara\'s alert management features\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>New Alerts Reports are available that outputs alerts based on defined parameters like client, device type and site, and can be scheduled to deliver on a recurring basis</li>\r\n	<li>Enhanced Alert Dashboard with user-defined views to see current or historical alerts and search capability</li>\r\n	<li>Revamped Alert Details Pages allow users to see summary information for an alert, related alerts and related tickets</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Alert-Management.jpg\" alt=\"Alert Management\" width=\"1024\" height=\"658\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-4753\" />\r\n<p>','Introducing Knowledge Base, Remote Multi-Console Sessions and More!','','publish','open','open','','introducing-knowledge-base-remote-multi-console-sessions','','','2014-09-19 04:52:21','2014-09-19 04:52:21','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=4720',0,'post','',0),(4732,36,'2014-09-09 05:47:09','2014-09-09 05:47:09','','DevOps-01','Enterprise DevOps Webinar','inherit','open','open','','devops-01','','','2014-09-09 05:47:09','2014-09-09 05:47:09','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/DevOps-01.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4738,31,'2014-09-09 10:26:54','2014-09-09 10:26:54','','Moving Up The Stack - Blog Post','','inherit','open','open','','moving-up-the-stack-blog-post','','','2014-09-09 10:26:54','2014-09-09 10:26:54','',4716,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Moving-Up-The-Stack-Blog-Post.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4739,31,'2014-09-09 10:28:03','2014-09-09 10:28:03','','Moving Up The Stack','','inherit','open','open','','moving-up-the-stack-blog-feed','','','2014-09-09 10:28:03','2014-09-09 10:28:03','',4716,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Moving-Up-The-Stack-Blog-Feed.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4748,31,'2014-09-10 04:37:10','2014-09-10 04:37:10','','Knowledge Base','','inherit','open','open','','knowledge-base-blog-post','','','2014-09-10 04:37:10','2014-09-10 04:37:10','',4720,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Knowledge-Base-Blog-Post.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4751,31,'2014-09-10 04:48:18','2014-09-10 04:48:18','','Remote Multi-Console Sessions','','inherit','open','open','','remote-multi-console-sessions-blog-post','','','2014-09-10 04:48:18','2014-09-10 04:48:18','',4720,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Remote-Multi-Console-Sessions-Blog-Post.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4753,31,'2014-09-10 07:04:52','2014-09-10 07:04:52','','Alert Management','','inherit','open','open','','alert-management-2','','','2014-09-10 07:05:41','2014-09-10 07:05:41','',4720,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Alert-Management.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4755,31,'2014-09-10 07:45:22','2014-09-10 07:45:22','','Remote Multi-Console Sessions','','inherit','open','open','','remote-multi-console-sessions-blog-feed','','','2014-09-10 07:45:40','2014-09-10 07:45:40','',4720,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Remote-Multi-Console-Sessions-Blog-Feed.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4767,1,'2014-09-10 17:03:45','2014-09-10 17:03:45','','Knowledge Base','','inherit','open','open','','knowledge-base','','','2014-09-10 17:04:12','2014-09-10 17:04:12','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Knowledge-Base.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4774,1,'2014-09-10 17:34:00','2014-09-10 17:34:00','','Vistara-Partner-Program-AAG','','inherit','open','open','','vistara-partner-program-aag','','','2014-09-10 17:34:00','2014-09-10 17:34:00','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Vistara-Partner-Program-AAG.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(4778,36,'2014-09-11 05:42:24','2014-09-11 05:42:24','','apachi_tomcat_tech_int','','inherit','open','open','','apachi_tomcat_tech_int-2','','','2014-09-11 05:42:24','2014-09-11 05:42:24','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/apachi_tomcat_tech_int1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4779,36,'2014-09-11 05:42:25','2014-09-11 05:42:25','','oracle_tech_int','','inherit','open','open','','oracle_tech_int','','','2014-09-11 05:42:25','2014-09-11 05:42:25','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/oracle_tech_int.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4780,36,'2014-09-11 05:42:26','2014-09-11 05:42:26','','supervisor_tech_int','','inherit','open','open','','supervisor_tech_int','','','2014-09-11 05:42:26','2014-09-11 05:42:26','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/supervisor_tech_int.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4784,31,'2014-09-16 00:46:43','2014-09-16 00:46:43','<section class=\"section\">\r\n<div class=\"container static-content\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div>\r\n<h1>Sales Engineer (Enterprise Software, San Jose, California)</h1>\r\n<p>Vistara is looking for a a Sales Engineer (SE) based in Northern California who will provide pre-sales technical support to Vistara Sales Reps and customers covering all of the company’s family of products in North America. The SE will perform pre-sales calls on prospective clients, participate in trade shows and events, and act as the technical account manager for existing customers. This is a technical position supporting Sales requiring strong IT infrastructure background and the ability to work with enterprise IT teams.</p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: 13px;\">Department:</strong> Sales</p>\r\n<p><strong>Title of the role:</strong> Sales Engineer</p>\r\n<p><strong>Location:</strong> San Jose, California</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reports to:</strong> Vice President of Sales</p>\r\n<p><h2>Responsibilities:</h2></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The Sales Engineer (SE) provides pre-sales technical support to Vistara Sales Reps (SR) and customers covering all of the company’s family of products.</li>\r\n	<li>The SE and SR work in tandem to formulate account strategies.</li>\r\n	<li>The SE makes pre-sales calls on prospective clients and is the focal point for customer evaluations, proof of concepts, and demos.</li>\r\n	<li>The SE is expected to stay abreast of current industry technology, trends, and competition.</li>\r\n	<li>The SE will spend a considerable amount of time talking to customers in small (round table) discussions as well as large (seminar) audiences.</li>\r\n	<li>The SE will work in tandem with the SR(s) in fulfilling sales goals and responding to RFI/RFPs.</li>\r\n	<li>The SE may act as a focal point in case of a technical post-sales escalation for current customers. Some travel will be required.</li>\r\n	<li>The SE will perform system deployment, installation, and integration of Vistara solutions in customer environments.</li>\r\n	<li>SE’s should be self-motivated, able to work well with multiple sales reps, and be creative in obtaining information and solving problems.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><h2>Requirements:</h2></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>5 years plus of experience supporting IT solutions into Mid-market, large enterprise accounts and complex organizations using consultative sales techniques.</li>\r\n	<li>5 years plus of infrastructure experience.</li>\r\n	<li>BS/BA in CS/EE a plus.</li>\r\n	<li>Strong Windows & VMWare skills.</li>\r\n	<li>Previous startup experience.</li>\r\n	<li>Familiarity with infrastructure related solutions from other competitors.</li>\r\n	<li>The SE must have excellent written and verbal communications skills.</li>\r\n	<li>The SE must be able to talk about technical subjects and deliver technical presentations to a wide array of audiences with both technical and non-technical backgrounds.</li>\r\n	<li>The SE must be able to transfer knowledge to inexperienced customers and VAR’s.</li>\r\n	<li>The SE must have a desire to learn new technologies and enjoy doing “hands-on” work with Vistara technology and other relevant technologies.</li>\r\n<li>The SE must possess various personal traits like excellent inter-personal skills, high energy, flexible, self- motivated, trustworthy, team player and dependable.</li>\r\n<li>Has excellent follow through skills.</li>\r\n<li>Must have experience with various operating systems including LINUX and Windows from a Systems Administrator perspective.</li>\r\n<li>Understanding of infrastructure monitoring and management.</li>\r\n<li>Travel: 25-75%</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><b>Who We Are: </b>Vistara provides a comprehensive SaaS solution that delivers IT operations lifecycle management spanning physical, virtual, cloud and application elements. Vistara enables enterprise IT and service providers to see their entire IT infrastructure, control across elements, automate management, and optimize availability, performance and capacity to drive unified IT operations. Headquartered in San Jose, California, Vistara sells directly and through our network of leading distributors and value added resellers.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>','Sales Engineer - West Coast (Enterprise Software, San Jose, California)','','publish','open','open','','sales-engineer-enterprise-software-san-jose-california','','','2014-11-06 12:24:44','2014-11-06 12:24:44','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?page_id=4784',0,'page','',0),(4804,1,'2014-09-17 23:54:47','2014-09-17 23:54:47','<img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Enterprise-DevOps-Blog-Post.jpg\" alt=\"Enterprise DevOps\" width=\"299\" height=\"224\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-4809\" /><p>This week <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/pub/venkat-etikyala/47/98b/635\">Venkat Etikyala</a>, Vistara\'s engineering director joined us to talk about the <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/company/resources/latestwebinars?commid=125695\">DevOps lessons that we\'ve learned in managing a highly distributed SaaS application</a>. Venkat discusses how we apply DevOps principles to break down barriers between development and operations and how the Vistara SaaS application enables rapid delivery, continuous and process-based governance, and closer alignment to customer needs.</p> \r\n\r\n<p> In this webinar, you will learn that <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/company/resources/latestwebinars?commid=125695\">Enterprise DevOps</a> is all about the culture and processes that enables continuous integration and delivery for a more agile business. <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/company/resources/latestwebinars?commid=125695\">Watch the 44 minute webinar</a> recording to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hear real-life examples on how we apply DevOps at a SaaS company</li>\r\n	<li>Learn how Vistara SaaS application helps us understand the performance and health of our highly dynamic infrastructure</li>\r\n	<li>See a live demo to catch some of these principles in action via the Vistara platform</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>To learn more, watch our webinar on <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/company/resources/latestwebinars?commid=125695\">Enterprise DevOps</a>. You can also view the slides from the webinar below.</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"margin-bottom: 5px;\"><strong style=\"font-size: 1.5em; line-height: 1.5em;\">Enterprise DevOps</strong></div>\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.slideshare.net/slideshow/embed_code/39157959\" width=\"427\" height=\"356\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" style=\"border:1px solid #CCC; border-width:1px; margin-bottom:5px; max-width: 100%;\" allowfullscreen> </iframe> <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px\"> <strong> <a href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/vistara/enterprise-devops-39157959\" title=\"Enterprise DevOps\" target=\"_blank\">Enterprise DevOps</a> </strong> from <strong><a href=\"http://www.slideshare.net/vistara\" target=\"_blank\">Vistara</a></strong> </div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-bottom: 5px;\"><strong style=\"font-size: 1.5em; line-height: 1.5em;\">Learn More! </strong></div>\r\nGo to our <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/solutions/devops-enablement/\">DevOps Enablement page</a> for more information on Vistara\'s capabilites. To understand how Vistara can align your infrastructure operations to business goals, <a href=\"http://info.vistarait.com/vistara-contact-us\">request a live demo</a> today!','Watch Our Recorded Webinar on Enterprise DevOps','','publish','open','open','','enterprise-devops-webinar','','','2014-09-19 04:45:42','2014-09-19 04:45:42','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=4804',0,'post','',0),(4809,31,'2014-09-18 00:13:31','2014-09-18 00:13:31','Enterprise DevOps','Enterprise DevOps','','inherit','open','open','','group-of-business-men-zz','','','2014-09-18 00:13:48','2014-09-18 00:13:48','',4804,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Enterprise-DevOps-Blog-Post.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4810,31,'2014-09-18 00:14:00','2014-09-18 00:14:00','Enterprise DevOps','Enterprise DevOps','','inherit','open','open','','group-of-business-men-zz-2','','','2014-09-18 00:14:12','2014-09-18 00:14:12','',4804,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Enterprise-DevOps-Blog-Feed.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4824,31,'2014-09-30 21:44:04','2014-09-30 21:44:04','<img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Shellshock-Blog-Post.jpg\" alt=\"Shellshock and IT Operations\" width=\"358\" height=\"237\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-4828\" /> <p>In the today’s IT environments, security vulnerabilities in industry standard software components have far reaching impact on enterprises. IT Operations must be always ready to respond to unanticipated changes. The recently identified vulnerability in bash - <a href=\"https://gigaom.com/2014/09/25/the-critical-shellshock-flaw-affects-many-linux-and-apple-systems-heres-what-you-need-to-know/\" target=\"_blank\">Shellshock</a> - is a case in point.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Addressing this critical vulnerability requires IT Operations teams to patch hundreds if not thousands of servers at a day’s notice. To accomplish this, IT Operations must be able to:</p> \r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Easily identify vulnerable servers,</li> \r\n	<li>Identify critical applications that are impacted,</li> \r\n        <li>Plan and apply appropriate change controls, and \r\n        <li>Automate patch deployment across identified infrastructure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Vistara faced this very challenge in the wake of Shellshock. We needed to patch all the infrastructure in our cloud on which Vistara runs. We used Vistara to identify vulnerable servers and automatically roll-out a patch within a few hours after <a href=\"http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2014-6271\" target=\"_blank\">Shellshock was first identified</a>. We secured our cloud and proactively notified customers even before they heard about Shellshock.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Incidents like Shellshock and HeartBleed highlight some key insights for IT Operations:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n        <li><b>Agility of response has become a critical competency.</b> Unpredictable changes are the norm in an interconnected world. The speed with which IT Operations can respond to changes has a significant impact on business outcomes.</li>\r\n        <li><b>Securing the management tool is easier with SaaS.</b> In contrast to traditional on-premise management tools, a SaaS based management tool like Vistara is completely managed by the solution provider. Customers can rest assured that their SaaS provider is keeping their tool secure.</li>\r\n        <li><b>SaaS based tools enable best practices to be easily shared and applied.</b> Using the same capabilities and approach that we used, customers are able to patch and secure their own environments.</li>  \r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Vistara enables IT teams to improve detection and apply standard processes and best practices across all enterprise systems. To learn more about Vistara and how it can help you respond to vulnerabilities like Shellshock, <a href=\"http://info.vistarait.com/vistara-contact-us\" target=\"_blank\">reach out for a personalized demo</a>.</p>','What Does Shellshock Mean for IT Operations','','publish','open','open','','shellshock-and-it-operations','','','2014-10-01 20:06:35','2014-10-01 20:06:35','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=4824',0,'post','',0),(4827,31,'2014-09-30 22:05:01','2014-09-30 22:05:01','','Shellshock and IT Operations','','inherit','open','open','','shellshock-blog-feed','','','2014-09-30 22:05:15','2014-09-30 22:05:15','',4824,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Shellshock-Blog-Feed.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4828,31,'2014-09-30 22:05:40','2014-09-30 22:05:40','','Shellshock and IT Operations','','inherit','open','open','','shellshock-blog-post','','','2014-09-30 22:05:53','2014-09-30 22:05:53','',4824,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Shellshock-Blog-Post.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4834,31,'2014-10-07 16:11:22','2014-10-07 16:11:22','<img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Life-Before-and-After-DevOps-Blog-Post.png\" alt=\"Life Before and After DevOps\" width=\"293\" height=\"224\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-4837\" /><p>We know that the new DevOps approach is changing the way software developers and operations interact and collaborate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What does that mean for the job of an IT Operations Manager? Let’s look at a day in the life before and after moving to a DevOps approach for an operations guy. Let’s call him Bob...</p> \r\n\r\n<p><b>Release Management</b></p> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Life Before DevOps… Bob had to be involved in every release. Dev teams had scripts they wanted and engineers need VMs to be provisioned and/or configured.</li> \r\n<li>Life After DevOps… VM provisioning and configurations are automated through config management recipes or scripts that are embedded with each code deployment, so Bob doesn’t get pulled into the tactical fire drills for releases.</li> \r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Monitoring Production Apps</b></p> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Life Before DevOps… Bob has multiple apps that are in production that he is responsible for once they go live. He is reactive to issues in the environment because they don’t appear on his radar before then.</li> \r\n<li>Life After DevOps… Because ops participated early in the process and he’s tracking the app from dev stage, Bob has insight into the potential performance issues from the outset and has been able to mitigate many of them, working with the developers.</li> \r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Scaling</b></p> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Life Before DevOps… New servers are being added by engineering all of the time. He may or may not know when they are added, but he sure is responsible for the performance of the environments.</li> \r\n<li>Life After DevOps… Automated scaling allows for new servers to be provisioned and configured. If he has a solution like Vistara, they’re automatically discovered and managed according to the rules he’s set, whether they are in dev, test or production.</li> \r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>While Bob’s day to day tasks have changed, he still needs the right tools to enable him to operate a dynamic infrastructure that supports dev, test and production environments and has to be managed with a service-centric view.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vistara is a highly distributed SaaS application and our engineers have organized around a DevOps approach. Hear Vistara’s DevOps lead talk about what we learned in the transition and how we manage our highly distributed SaaS app <a href=\"https://www.brighttalk.com/webcast/11747/125695\" target=\"_blank\">eating our own dogfood.</a></p> \r\n\r\n<p>Also, don’t miss the <a href=\"https://www.brighttalk.com/webcast/11747/129241\" target=\"_blank\">upcoming webinar with DevOps visionary Rob Berger</a>.','IT Ops - Life Before and After DevOps','','publish','open','open','','life-before-and-after-devops','','','2014-10-07 16:34:15','2014-10-07 16:34:15','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=4834',0,'post','',0),(4837,31,'2014-10-07 16:21:33','2014-10-07 16:21:33','','Life Before and After DevOps ','','inherit','open','open','','life-before-and-after-devops-blog-post','','','2014-10-07 16:21:51','2014-10-07 16:21:51','',4834,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Life-Before-and-After-DevOps-Blog-Post.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4838,31,'2014-10-07 16:24:03','2014-10-07 16:24:03','','Life Before and After DevOps','','inherit','open','open','','life-before-and-after-devops-blog-feed','','','2014-10-07 16:24:20','2014-10-07 16:24:20','',4834,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Life-Before-and-After-DevOps-Blog-Feed.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4847,36,'2014-10-09 06:20:02','2014-10-09 06:20:02','','Slider-6-BG-01','','inherit','open','open','','slider-6-bg-01','','','2014-10-09 06:20:02','2014-10-09 06:20:02','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Slider-6-BG-01.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4850,36,'2014-10-09 06:50:28','2014-10-09 06:50:28','','Register now-03','','inherit','open','open','','register-now-03','','','2014-10-09 06:50:28','2014-10-09 06:50:28','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Register-now-03.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4854,36,'2014-10-10 05:09:17','2014-10-10 05:09:17','','Request-for-demo','','inherit','open','open','','request-for-demo','','','2014-10-10 05:09:17','2014-10-10 05:09:17','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Request-for-demo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4856,43,'2014-10-16 06:50:04','2014-10-16 06:50:04','','Video player','','inherit','open','open','','video-player','','','2014-10-16 06:50:04','2014-10-16 06:50:04','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Video-player.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4857,43,'2014-10-16 07:04:49','2014-10-16 07:04:49','','closeBtn','','inherit','open','open','','closebtn','','','2014-10-16 07:04:49','2014-10-16 07:04:49','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/closeBtn.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4859,31,'2014-10-17 02:08:05','2014-10-17 02:08:05','<img src=\"http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Rob-Berger-Blog-Post.jpg\" alt=\"In Conversation With Rob Berger\" width=\"224\" height=\"224\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-4863\" /><p>The technology industry is well known for incessantly promoting the next big thing. So much so, <a href=\"http://blogs.wsj.com/digits/2014/09/18/larry-ellison-has-a-long-list-of-memorable-quotes/\" target=\"_blank\">Larry Ellison</a> famously remarked in 2008, \"The computer industry is the only industry that is more fashion-driven than women\'s fashion.\" As a technology executive who\'s witnessed one hype cycle after another, you might be right in discounting all the buzz around DevOps. \r\n\r\n<p> That would be a big mistake! Industry thought leader <a href=\"https://twitter.com/rberger\" target=\"_blank\">Rob Berger</a> shares in our webinar why DevOps matters for enterprises and startups alike. In an interactive conversation with Vistara CTO, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/varma1\" target=\"_blank\">Varma Kunaparaju</a>, Rob states, \"DevOps is not a role or job description but a philosophy of doing things...DevOps is about applying agile and lean techniques in IT operations for meeting business goals\". DevOps demands continuous collaboration between Dev, Ops, and business teams across the product lifecycle which can be a difficult transformation for most enterprises.</p> \r\n\r\n<p> Rob\'s advice to IT leaders who are looking to implement DevOps is to tie internal performance measures to broader organizational metrics so you can leverage the skills of people across different teams. Watch the <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/company/resources/latestwebinars?commid=129241\" target=\"_blank\">IT Visionaries Webinar</a> to hear more practical advice from Rob.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are highlights from Rob:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You need Devs to take responsibility for their production app. Have Devs rotate on pager duty for at least some of the time. Devs will then learn how of some of the decisions they take create pain on the production side.</li>\r\n	<li>Tie in your DevOps initiatives to top level business metrics. To accomplish a business metric, what does it take in the infrastructure?</li>\r\n	<li>One of the key things in DevOps is to automate all things. As an Ops person, you have to learn how to script and use tools like Chef, Puppet, or Ansible for configuration management. When you want to bring up a new service, it should require little to no manual intervention.</li>\r\n        <li>Enterprises need to figure out how they can push evolution without disrupting day to day operations. One technique for adopting DevOps is to start small. Identify projects where you can create new teams to work on modular initiatives.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Watch the <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/company/resources/latestwebinars?commid=129241\" target=\"_blank\">full presentation</a> for Rob\'s insights on doing DevOps right!</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"margin-bottom: 5px;\"><strong style=\"font-size: 1.5em; line-height: 1.5em;\">Learn More! </strong></div>\r\nVisit our <a href=\"http://www.vistarait.com/solutions/devops-enablement/\" target=\"_blank\">DevOps Enablement page</a> on how Vistara supports applications built on dynamic infrastructure and services. If you would like to learn more about Vistara, <a href=\"http://info.vistarait.com/vistara-contact-us\">request a live demo</a> today!','DevOps Is For Real and Rob Berger Tells Us Why','','publish','open','open','','devops-with-rob-berger','','','2014-10-17 16:50:57','2014-10-17 16:50:57','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/?p=4859',0,'post','',0),(4863,31,'2014-10-17 02:17:50','2014-10-17 02:17:50','','In Conversation With Rob Berger ','','inherit','open','open','','rob-berger-blog-post','','','2014-10-17 02:18:14','2014-10-17 02:18:14','',4859,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Rob-Berger-Blog-Post.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4864,31,'2014-10-17 02:18:42','2014-10-17 02:18:42','','In Conversation With Rob Berger ','','inherit','open','open','','rob-berger-blog-feed','','','2014-10-17 02:18:52','2014-10-17 02:18:52','',4859,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/Rob-Berger-Blog-Feed.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4872,36,'2014-10-17 05:28:51','2014-10-17 05:28:51','','watch now-03','','inherit','open','open','','watch-now-03','','','2014-10-17 05:28:51','2014-10-17 05:28:51','',0,'http://www.vistarait.com/wp-content/uploads/watch-now-03.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4875,36,